<p><strong>And Finally&hellip;</strong></p>
<p><em>[BBC]</em></p>
<p>Teachers have complained about <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/education-35716523">&ldquo;cheating watches&rdquo;</a> being sold online for &pound;40-50 to give students an unfair advantage in exams.&nbsp; The watches hold data or written information include an &ldquo;emergency button&rdquo; to quickly switch from hidden text to a clock face.</p>
<p>And off-topic but great fun is the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IvUU8joBb1Q">Marble Machine</a> &ndash; a music instrument that uses 2000 marbles and one musician frantically cranking a handle.</p>
