</li>
<li>
<p>Twitter has <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/33907611/say-goodbye-to-twitters-140-character-limit-for-direct-messages">removed the 140 character limit</a> on Direct Messages.&nbsp; [BBC]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>&hellip;but Carl Miller examines how <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/twitter/11841832/Is-the-140-character-limit-holding-Twitter-back.html">the 140 character limit may be holding Twitter back</a>.&nbsp; [The Telegraph]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/08/19/dropbox-now-lets-you-drag-and-drop-urls-to-share-webpages/">Dropbox now lets you drag and drop URLs</a> on any device to share webpages.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Good advice from Katie Sherwin on the use of (and design for) <a href="http://www.nngroup.com/articles/touchscreen-screen-readers/?utm_source=Alertbox&utm_campaign=e36a8f2c26-Paper_Ptype_Touch_Screen_Readers_1015_08_31_2015&utm_medium=email&utm_term=0_7f29a2b335-e36a8f2c26-24324137">screen readers on touchscreen devices</a>.&nbsp; [NNG]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Kenya is rolling out flat-packed <a href="http://www.gizmag.com/aleutia-solar-classroom-in-a-box-kenya/38808/">classrooms-in-a-box</a>, each with 11 solar-powered computers.&nbsp; [Audrey Watters]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The <a href="http://ssa.nls.uk/">Scottish Screen Archive</a> preserves and provides access to over 100 years of Scottish history on film and video.&nbsp; [NLS]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Google Maps now offers <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/09/02/google-maps-adds-curated-restaurant-recommendations-in-nyc-san-francisco-and-london">curated restaurant recommendations for London</a>, NYC and San Francisco.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The Polaroid Snap is a compact <a href="http://www.wired.com/2015/09/polaroid-ammunition-camera/?mbid=social_twitter">digital camera with a built in printer</a> that uses dye crystals in the paper rather than ink.&nbsp; [Wired]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Ofcom has released an online tool that lets people see what kind of <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-33906048">voice, 3G and 4G mobile coverage</a> they should be getting.&nbsp; [BBC]</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p><strong>And Finally&hellip;</strong></p>
<p><em>[TechCrunch]</em></p>
<p>Hershey has released the <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2015/09/16/likeachocolateselfie/">CocoJet 3D printer</a> to allow confectionery connoisseurs to print the design of their choice in chocolate.&nbsp; Consumers can choose from a library of 3D graphics on an iPad to get the machine to form a number of chocolate designs or, because the patterns are opensource, bespoke designs can also be uploaded to the CocoJet.&nbsp; It all looks a bit prototypish at the moment but, if you simply can&rsquo;t wait, you could own Choc Edge&rsquo;s &pound;2,000 <a href="http://www.chocedge.com/">Choc Creator 2.0</a> right now.</p>]]></description>
