<p>April fool pranks work well with young kids but can often become more cheesy as we move up the age range.&nbsp; This example from <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P2SsIYEbCio">assistant professor of mathematics and computer science, Matthew Weathers</a>, deserves a mention simply for the choreography and technical skills involved, plus the positive reception from his audience at Biola University, California.</p>]]></description>
