<li>The Guardian has launched a SecureDrop system <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/jun/05/guardian-launches-securedrop-whistleblowers-documents">for whistleblowers to share files</a> &ldquo;while avoiding most common forms of online tracking&rdquo;.&nbsp; [The Guardian]</li>
<li>Youworkforthem allows users to <a href="http://blog.youworkforthem.com/2014/05/27/install-fonts-ipad-iphone/">install additional fonts onto iOS 7 devices</a>.&nbsp; [Youworkforthem]</li>
<li>Sage advice from Theresa MacPhail for first-time authors: <a href="https://chroniclevitae.com/news/529-dear-first-time-author-how-to-turn-your-dissertation-into-a-book">how to turn your dissertation into a book</a>.&nbsp; [The Chronicle]</li>
<li>A server at Emory University in the US accidentally sent a <a href="http://thenextweb.com/shareables/2014/05/16/emory-university-server-accidentally-sends-reformat-request-windows-pcs-including/">reformat request to all Windows PCs</a>, including itself.&nbsp; [TNW]</li>
</ul>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p><strong>And Finally&hellip;</strong></p>
<p>World Cup fever is alive and kicking (sorry) and it provides opportunities for organisations to present us with information in a variety of visual and interactive ways.&nbsp; Judge for yourself whether you think these are more at the style or substance end of the spectrum:</p>
<ul>
<li>Google has released <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2014/06/05/google-launches-street-view-imagery-for-all-12-world-cup-stadiums-in-brazil">Street View imagery of all 12 World Cup stadiums</a> plus &ldquo;hundreds of interesting sites across Brazil&rdquo;</li>
<li>The Guardian presents an interactive guide to <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2014/may/30/-sp-world-cup-kits">World Cup kits through the ages</a> (HTML5)</li>
<li>TikiToki offers a <a href="http://www.tiki-toki.com/timeline/entry/300326/History-of-the-World-Cup#vars!date=1912-01-03_18:26:54!">timeline of World Cup historic facts</a></li>
<li>The Daily Mail offers a 2014 <a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/worldcup2014/article-2650824/World-Cup-squad-comparison-tool-Use-interactive-guide-32-teams-comes-top.html">World Cup squad comparison tool</a> (HTML5)</li>
<li>The BBC considers <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/guides/zgg334j#z22qq6f">what makes the perfect penalty?</a></li>
<li>And McDonalds allows you to pick and run your own <a href="http://en.mcdonalds.fantasy.fifa.com/">fantasy World Cup team</a></li>
</ul>
<p>But if you have no interest whatsoever in football, you might be entertained by these <a href="http://www.cultofmac.com/280795/watching-kids-trying-figure-use-old-apple-ii-totally-hilarious/">kids trying to work out how to use an old Apple II computer</a>.</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Mon, 16 Jun 2014 13:18:14 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
                    <item>
              <title>e-Learning Digest No 117 - May 14</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8753</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/8753</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>UK </strong><strong>Conferences &amp; Workshops&nbsp;</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1-6 Jun, London, <a href="http://www.nngroup.com/training/london">Nielsen Norman Usability Week</a>.&nbsp; [NNG]</li>
<li>10 Jun, Bradford, <a href="https://www.regonline.com/builder/site/?eventid=1525551">Team-based Learning (TBL): Group Work that Engages Students</a>.&nbsp; [ALT]</li>
<li>10 Jun, Derby, <a href="http://www.heacademy.ac.uk/events/detail/2014/10_June_Online_assessment_CLL">Changing the Learning Landscape - Online Assessment</a>.&nbsp; [HEA]</li>
<li>10-11 Jun, Walton Hall, <a href="http://kn.open.ac.uk/public/workspace.cfm?wpid=9790">The Computers and Learning Research Group Conference</a>.&nbsp; [Canan Blake]</li>
