<li>The <a href="http://www.einstein.caltech.edu/index.html">Einstein Papers Project</a> is digitizing 14,000 pages of papers, lectures, research notes, interviews, and letters.&nbsp; [Zite]</li>
<li><a href="http://www.kineo.com/blog/news/new-community-site-launched-for-adapt-open-source-elearning-project">Adapt</a> is an open source framework created by Kineo to develop mobile learning that runs across desktops, smartphones and tablets.&nbsp; [Kineo]</li>
<li>The latest JD Power tablet study shows <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2013/11/01/jd-power-explains-why-samsung-beat-apple-in-its-latest-tablet-study-price/?ncid=tcdaily">Samsung edging ahead of iPad</a>, due mainly to their price differential.&nbsp; [TechCrunch]</li>
<li>Matthew Reisz wonders if <a href="http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/features/feature-scholars-rude-awakenings/2008689.article">academic bitchiness</a> serves any useful scholarly purpose.&nbsp; [THE]</li>
<li>Med Kharbach suggests <a href="http://www.educatorstechnology.com/2013/11/7-wonderful-ipad-apps-to-learn-about.html">7 iPad apps to learn about human body in 3D</a>.&nbsp; [Educators Technology]</li>
<li>The BBC aims to support a new generation of programmers by making <a href="http://www.agent4change.net/events/event/2121-bbc-makes-2015-year-of-making-and-coding.html">2015 a year of &lsquo;making and coding&rsquo;</a>.&nbsp; [MJO]</li>
<li>Gordon Ritter suggests that education (along with healthcare) stand out as the most <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2013/10/26/are-you-in-a-cloud-friendly-industry/">cloud-friendly industries</a>.&nbsp; [Matthew Moran]</li>
