<p><br /><strong>Tags</strong>: information literacy, information media literacy, alfabetizzazione informativa,<br /><br /><strong>context</strong><br /><br />Describe the material and social characteristics of the environment in which you operate.<br />Where will your project take place? Who are the main actors involved? Include images,<br />videos, sketches - anything that would help others understand the opportunities and<br />constraints you are dealing with.<br />Descrivere le caratteristiche del materiale e sociale del contesto in cui si opera. Dove si<br />effettua il vostro progetto? Chi sono i principali attori coinvolti? Include immagini, video,<br />disegni - tutto ci&ograve; che aiuta gli altri a capire le opportunit&agrave; e i vincoli che si stanno trattando.<br /><br /><strong>ENGLISH</strong> (automatic translate) sorry :-)<br /><br />Contesto: academic instituction &ndash; university library<br />Users= Students Facolt&agrave; di Scienze della Formazione - Corso di Laurea Scienze della<br />Formazione primaria<br /><br />caract&eacute;ristique: dominated by women, many students work in primary schools.<br /><br />Project<br />Help students find, use, make informed choices in network information systems according to their information needs and in particular recognize and use the resources available through the university library system.<br /><br /><strong>Today</strong><br />Workshop for 35 people<br />Face to face<br />Time: 20 h (5 meetings of 4 h)<br />Members: 35<br />Teamwork<br />Tools: google drive, dropbox, blog, sw freemind, sw cmap<br /><br />Final report= The report describes the research experience.<br /><br /><strong>In the future</strong><br />MOOC<br />users= all students<br /><br /><strong>SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES</strong><br /><br />What resources are available in the portal Unifi (University of Florence)<br />how they are organized<br />how to use<br />when use<br />what services are available<br /><br />Two levels of preparation: basic, advanced<br /><br /><strong>OBJECTIVES</strong>: <strong>General Level</strong><br /><br />- Create awareness that information systems are many and diverse (OPAC, databases, search engineers, digital library, open archives, etc.).&gt; Does not exist just Google&gt; deep web, Every information system has its own characteristics&gt; concept COMPLEXITY 'of Network&gt; sense of loss<br /><br />- Information systems are chosen based on their information needs:<br /><br />you already have a bibliography<br />you have to create a bibliography<br />you must find a text<br />you should find an article, etc..<br /><br />- Main features of information systems&gt; concept: Dissolve the complexity&gt; have reference<br /><br />Research is a process<br /><br /><strong>OBJECTIVES: general level of standards:</strong><br />1) <em>Know how research works in the catalogs</em><br />2) Know how research works in the database etc..<br />There are as many levels as there are specific general information systems that you want to<br />deal<br /><br />1) <em>Research in Catalogue / OPACs</em> (example)<br /><br />- What there in the catalog<br /><br />- When you have to use a catalog<br /><br />- Functions of the Catalogue (FRBR)<br /><br />- 1 record = 1 description of the resource<br /><br />- Record: how did the record of a catalog: descriptive fields, semantic fields, fields<br />administrative&gt; Interoperability<br /><br />- The records are not all alike: monograph and serials. (location, consistency)<br /><br />- Ownership vs. access<br /><br />- How to access the electronic resource: the SFX service<br /><br />Search the OPAC<br />WHERE: The search is performed in the metadata (resource description)&gt; Choosing Keywords<br />+ tools of the trade (AND, OR, etc.).<br /><br />Types of research: basic, advanced, lists, fields<br /><br />Search Modality: keywords, scrolling, navigation links<br /><br />authority file<br /><br />intelligence of the system: DDC, Subject, etc..<br /><br 